other_tests.findings: Testis with seminiferous tubules lined by Sertoli cells but no germ cells. Dense peritubular fibrosis, with prominent Leydig cells in the stroma. Evidence of a small cell malignant neoplasm with small round or fusiform cells and increased mitotic activity.
Mainly testicular tissue with an ovarian cortex containing a few follicles.
other_tests.changes_over_time: No further evidence of malignancy was found despite numerous sections.
